@@gHISTORY@@W

The interior history of the Martial Artist tradition is a long argument
between two schools that spent generations insisting they had nothing to
learn from each other. Monks held that the Interior Forms -- the discipline
of breath, posture, and applied understanding developed in the mountain
monasteries -- were complete in themselves. Brawlers, who emerged from the
fighting pits and harbor circuits where formal theory held no authority,
held that no system survived first contact with an opponent who fought
without rules. The synthesis came not from agreement but from repeated
failure on both sides: monasteries lost students to the pit circuits, and
experienced pit fighters could not reliably overcome a trained Monk. Those
who trained in both found the disciplines did not cancel but complete each
other -- the Brawler's ferocity supplied entry pressure the Forms lacked
in chaotic encounters, while the Monk's structural timing turned that
ferocity into something sustainable. The first Martial Artists had spent
two apprenticeships learning two halves of a single method.

@@gMARTIAL ARTIST@@W

Martial Artists are the perfected union of @@gMonk@@W discipline and @@gBrawler@@W
ferocity. They weaponize breath, balance, and impact timing, turning every
exchange into a rhythm of pressure, recovery, and sudden burst.

To become a Martial Artist, you must master either @@gMonk@@W or @@gBrawler@@W
(remort prerequisites for the adept path).

@@gPassive class advantages@@W
Martial Artist grants several always-on combat bonuses as adept levels rise:

  1) @@wChi-technique damage bonus@@W
     - Chi attacks in the palmstrike/pummel/aurabolt family gain extra damage.
     - Scaling: +2.5% damage per Martial Artist adept level (up to +50% at 20).

  2) @@wBare-hand strike damage bonus@@W
     - Unarmed direct-hit damage is increased while using bare-hand combat.
     - Scaling: +2% damage per Martial Artist adept level (up to +40% at 20).

  3) @@wExtra attack round@@W
     - Having any Martial Artist adept level grants an additional melee hit in
       the multi-hit calculation.

@@gUnique Martial Artist mechanics@@W
  * @@wMartial stance@@W becomes available with the adept path.
  * While Martial Artist adept is active, your maximum chi pool is raised to
    @@w25@@W (supporting longer chi-combo windows).
  * Martial Artist uses @@wConstitution@@W as its adept prime attribute and
    follows a durable, sustained-melee growth profile.

@@gMartial Artist reincarnation bonuses@@W
Each Martial Artist adept reincarnation grants passive advantages:

  * @@wDirect-hit damage@@W: +2% per Martial Artist adept reincarnation.
  * At @@w20+ Martial Artist adept reincarnations@@W, your chi cap remains at
    @@w25@@W even without active Martial adept levels.
  * At @@w20+ Martial Artist adept reincarnations@@W, combo capacity gains
    +1 slot when combo progression is active.

In short: Martial Artist is the chi-pressure adept, excelling at sustained
unarmed aggression with strong burst conversion when resources are spent well.

